Matplotlib :- Matplotlib is an amazing visualization liberary in python for 2D and 3D plots of arrays.

It was introduced by john Hunter in the year 2002.

Plot Types :-

  1. Linear Plot
  2. Scatter Plot
  3. Bar Plot
  4. Stem Plot
  5. Hist Plot
  6. Box Plot
  7. Step Plot
  8. Pie Plot
  9. Fill_Between_Plot
In[2]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In[7]:
# Ex - 

x = [1,2,3,4]
y = [5,6,7,8]

plt.plot(x,y)        # By default Linear Graph
plt.show()

In[40]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
In[47]:
x = ["Car","Bike","Scooty","Bicycle"]
y = [40,85,75,35]
z = [20,30,40,15]

width = 0.2

p = np.arange(len(x))       # Most line (Not arrange ---> arange)
p1 = [j+ width for j in p]

plt.title("Parking Survey")
plt.xlabel("Vehicles")
plt.ylabel("Numbers")

# c=['Red','Yellow','Green','Magenta']

plt.bar(p, y, width=0.2, color='r', edgecolor="Blue")    # Seprate bar plots apply
plt.bar(p1, z, width=0.2, color='g', edgecolor="Blue")
plt.show()
